
[1]agrom

   A'GROM, n. a disease frequent in Bengal, and other parts of the E.
   Indies, in which the tongue chaps and cleaves, becomes rough and
   sometimes covered with white spots. The remedy is some chalybeate
   liquor, or the juice of mint.
